HEADWORD: candyweed
<hw>can"dy*weed`</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧n"d⟦esl⟧*w⟦emac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>bog plant (<spn>Polygala lutea</spn>) of pine barrens of
southeastern U.S. having spikes of irregular yellow-orange
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> orange milkwort, yellow milkwort, yellow bachelor's
button.</syn>⟦br⟧
